==演化學觀點==
女性自慰會改變陰道、子宮頸和子宮的环境條件，改變受孕的機會，這取決於自慰的時間。女性受精前1分鐘至45分鐘後之間達到高潮較有利於精子到達她的卵子。如果她與多於一名男性性交，這樣可能会增加他們其中一个射出的精子到達卵子，以至受精懷孕的可能性<ref>{{cite book |last=Baker |first=Robin |title=[[精子戰爭|Sperm Wars: The Science of Sex]] |publisher=Diane Books Publishing Company |date=1996-06 |isbn=978-0-7881-6004-2}}</ref><ref name=Ejaculate_manipulation_by_females>{{cite journal |last=Baker |first=Robin R. |author2=Bellis, Mark A. |date=1993-11 |title=Human sperm competition: Ejaculate manipulation by females and a function for the female orgasm. |journal=Animal Behaviour |volume=46 |issue=5 |pages=87, 23p |doi=10.1006/anbe.1993.1272}}</ref>。也可以通過女性自慰時所增加宮頸粘液酸度以保護宮頸免受感染。

男性自慰會把舊的低[[能動性|能動性]]精子從男性的生殖道去除，下一次射精時的精子會更新更好，令性交時達到受孕的可能性增加。如果女性與多於一名男性性交，具有最高活力的{{Link-en|精子的競爭力|Sperm competition}}会較高<ref>{{cite journal |author = Thomsen, Ruth |title = Sperm Competition and the Function of Masturbation in Japanese Macaques |publisher = Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München |date = 2000-10 |url = http://edoc.ub.uni-muenchen.de/105/ |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160814155946/https://edoc.ub.uni-muenchen.de/105/ |archivedate = 2016-08-14 |access-date = 2016-07-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last= Baker |first=Robin R.|author2=Bellis, Mark A. |date=1993-11 |title=Human sperm competition: Ejaculate adjustment by males and the function of masturbation. |journal=Animal Behaviour |volume=46 |issue=5 |pages=861, 25p |doi=10.1006/anbe.1993.1271}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Shackelford |first=Todd K. |author2=Goetz, Aaron T. |date=2007-02 |title=Adaptation to Sperm Competition in Humans. |journal=Current Directions in Psychological Science |volume=16 |issue=1 |pages=47–50 |url=http://rcgd.isr.umich.edu/seminars/Fall2013/Fall13_articles/Shackelford_Goetz_CD_2007.pdf |doi=10.1111/j.1467-8721.2007.00473.x |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304101826/http://rcgd.isr.umich.edu/seminars/Fall2013/Fall13_articles/Shackelford_Goetz_CD_2007.pdf |archivedate=2016-03-04 |author= |access-date=2016-07-17 }}</ref>。

