一小部分男性患有[[性高潮後病情症候群|性高潮後病情症候群]]（POIS），患者無論通过自慰或性交射精，之後可能會感到全身肌肉嚴重疼痛，以及其他相关的症狀，症狀可持續長達一周<ref name=Balon2005>{{cite book |title=Handbook of Sexual Dysfunction |url=https://archive.org/details/handbookofsexual0000unse_d3f6 |publisher=Taylor & Francis |veditors=Balon R, Segraves RT |year=2005 |isbn=978-0-8247-5826-4}}</ref><ref name=Wylie2015>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oH64CAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA75&dq=Post%20orgaasmic%20illness%20syndrome&pg=PA75#v=onepage&q=Post-orgasmic%20illness%20syndrome&f=false |title=ABC of Sexual Health |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |year=2015 |page=75 |isbn=978-1-118-66556-5 |editor=Wylie KR |accessdate=2015-10-21 |archive-date=2020-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105024937/https://books.google.com/books?id=oH64CAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA75&dq=Post%20orgaasmic%20illness%20syndrome&pg=PA75#v=onepage&q=Post-orgasmic%20illness%20syndrome&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=GARD>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Postorgasmic illness syndrome |encyclopedia=Genetic and Rare Diseases Information Center (GARD) |publisher=National Institutes of Health |accessdate=2015-07-30 |year=2015 |url=https://rarediseases.info.nih.gov/gard/10809/postorgasmic-illness-syndrome/resources/1 |deadurl=yes |format=html |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305193016/https://rarediseases.info.nih.gov/gard/10809/postorgasmic-illness-syndrome/resources/1 |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref>。一些醫生推測性高潮後病情症候群在民眾中出現的机率可能比已經在學術文獻中報告的更大<ref name=Ashby2010>{{cite journal |url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1743-6109.2010.01707.x/abstract;jsessionid=EC000313CA779834B8938F5F698E5FD3.f03t04 |title=Postorgasm illness syndrome--a spectrum of illnesses. |vauthors=Ashby J, Goldmeier D |journal=J Sex Med. |date=2010-05 |volume=7 |issue=5 |pages=1976–81 |doi=10.1111/j.1743-6109.2010.01707 |pmid=20214722 |deadurl=no |format=html |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221024829/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1743-6109.2010.01707.x/abstract%3Bjsessionid%3DEC000313CA779834B8938F5F698E5FD3.f03t04 |archivedate=2016-12-21 |access-date=2016-07-16 }}</ref>，而且許多性高潮後病情症候群患者尚未確診<ref name=McMahon2014>{{cite journal |url=https://www.statusplus.net/issm/saopaulo2014/presentations/082.pdf |title=Post-Orgasmic Illness Syndrome |author=McMahon CG |journal=16th World Meeting on Sexual Medicine |date=2014-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304110554/https://www.statusplus.net/issm/saopaulo2014/presentations/082.pdf |archivedate=2016-03-04 |access-date=2016-07-16 }}</ref>。

強迫自慰和其他強迫行為可能是情感問題顯現出來的跡象，這可能需要由精神衛生專家來解決<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vpul.upenn.edu/ohe/library/Sexhealth/articles/masturbating.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820190232/http://www.vpul.upenn.edu/ohe/library/Sexhealth/articles/masturbating.htm|archivedate=2010-08-20|title=University of Pennsylvania Office of Health Education article on masturbation|publisher=Vpul.upenn.edu|accessdate=2011-05-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。對於任何「神经質的習慣」，思考強迫行為的原因比試圖壓制自慰更有幫助<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chmed.com/behavioral-care/child-development/masturbation/ |title=Children's Medical Office of North Andover, P.C. article on Masturbation in Early Childhood |publisher=Chmed.com |accessdate=2011-05-29 |archive-date=2021-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405024213/https://www.chmed.com/behavioral-care/child-development/masturbation/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

青少年自慰有助於他們掌握性衝動的感覺，而且它会在前青春期及青春期期間的身體和情感發展中發揮作用<ref name=Datta>{{cite book|author=Parul Datta|title=Pediatric Nursing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Um1_7gM-E1wC&lpg=PA189&pg=PA189#v=onepage&q&f=false|publisher=Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers|year=2007|accessdate=2011-08-27|page=189|archive-date=2016-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227171317/https://books.google.com/books?id=Um1_7gM-E1wC&lpg=PA189&pg=PA189#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。嬰兒和幼兒会把生殖器像自己的耳朵或腳趾一樣拿來玩耍，如果這樣的玩耍成為常態，就應尋找背後的根本原因，比如孩子感到緊張及需要安慰、其他人反應過度、尿路感染、过於無聊、醫学問題、不適合其年齡的性知識、早熟、參與性化的遊戲、被性暴力對待（sexualized aggression）、被性挑逗。<ref name=Myers>{{cite book|author=John E. B. Myers|title=Myers on Evidence in Child, Domestic and Elder Abuse Cases, Volume 1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-krZZF9dl-sC&pg=PA385&dq=excessive+masturbation&hl=en&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8|quote=Jon Conte and his colleagues were interested to learn what factors are important to mental health professionals who regularly evaluate children for sexual abuse. The evaluators were asked to rank the importance of forty-one indicators of sexual abuse. The following indicators were thought important by more than ninety percent of evaluators: medical evidence of abuse, age-inappropriate sexual knowledge, sexualized play during the interview, precocious or seductive behavior, excessive masturbation, child's description is consistent over time, child's description reveals pressure or coercion.|publisher=Aspen Publishers|year=2005|accessdate=2011-08-27|page=385|archive-date=2021-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405024222/https://books.google.com/books?id=-krZZF9dl-sC&pg=PA385&dq=excessive+masturbation&hl=en&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Faller>{{cite book|author=Kathleen Coulborn Faller|title=Understanding and Assessing Child Sexual Maltreatment|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FkT2wTGTUAoC&pg=PA39&dq=%22excessive+masturbation%22&hl=en&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3|quote=Six different types of sexual behavior that signal possible sexual abuse will be described in this section: (a) excessive masturbation, (b) sexual interaction with peers, (c) sexual aggression toward younger or more naive children, (d) sexual accosting of older people or adults, (e) seductive behavior, and (f) promiscuity.|publisher=[[Sage_Publications|Sage Publications]]|year=2003|accessdate=2011-08-27|page=39|archive-date=2021-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405024234/https://books.google.com/books?id=FkT2wTGTUAoC&pg=PA39&dq=%22excessive+masturbation%22&hl=en&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3|dead-url=no}}</ref>

