t medical opinions] {{Wayback|url=http://www.religioustolerance.org/masturba1.htm |date=20210321144243 }} Ontario Consultants on Religious Tolerance. New URL: http://sites.google.com/site/completebaby/repression {{Wayback|url=http://sites.google.com/site/completebaby/repression |date=20210405024331 }}</ref>，「自慰：人類最初的性活動。在十九世紀它是種疾病，在二十世紀它是種解藥<ref name="Szasz"/>。」1991年6月第十届世界性科学大会召開之時，荷兰卫生、文化和社会部部长隨即在其开幕式上宣告：「自慰以前被认为是一种病态，但现在认为无害甚至是健康的行为。如果某人有性问题，那他不会是自慰者，而恰恰是那些不能自慰的人！」<ref name="中国性科学 史成礼 2011"/>

1994年，美國三藩市的一名外科醫生喬伊斯林·埃爾德斯指出，應把「自慰無害且安全」納入學校[[課程|課程]]之中，但最終因反對者斷言她在推广如何自慰而被迫辭職<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jackinworld.com/resources/general-articles/our-hero-dr-joycelyn-elders |title=JackinLibrary: Joycelyn Elders |publisher=Jackinworld.com |accessdate=2011-05-29 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120173033/http://www.jackinworld.com/resources/general-articles/our-hero-dr-joycelyn-elders |archivedate=2016-01-20 }}</ref>。

====21世紀====
在21世紀，自慰的實踐和文化觀點仍是不斷在變化，部分可歸因於科技的發展。例如數碼照片或實況影片使得人們可跟他人播送或互相直播自己的自慰經歷。跟[[遠程性愛|遠程性愛]]有關的科技仍在發展<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.askmen.com/sex/sex_toys_and_games/are-teledildonics-the-future-of-sex-toys.html|title=Are Teledildonics The Future Of Sex Toys?|publisher=AskMen|date=2016-01-17|accessdate=2017-01-16|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160512110812/http://www.askmen.com/sex/sex_toys_and_games/are-teledildonics-the-future-of-sex-toys.html|archivedate=2016-05-12}}</ref>。在[[BBC|BBC]]的電視節目《21世紀的愛》（Love in the 21st Century）中，自慰仍能直接地用作當中一集的名字<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/love-in-the-21st-century/episode-guide/|title=Love in the-21st-century episode guide|accessdate=2017-01-16|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407054407/http://www.channel4.com/programmes/love-in-the-21st-century/episode-guide|archivedate=2016-04-07}}</ref>。

===污名化===
儘管許多醫療專業人員和科學家發現大量證據表明自慰是健康無害的<ref name="Merck" /><ref name="Szasz" /><ref name="Shpancer2010" /><ref name="Coon2010" /><ref name="Sigel2004" /><ref name="Wood2005" /><ref name="Ley2014" /><ref name="Strassberg2015">{{cite book|last1=Strassberg|first1=Donald S.|last3=Perelman|first3=Michael A.|last2=Mackaronis|first2=Julia E.|year=2015|chapter=Sexual dysfunctions|chapterurl=https://books.google.nl/books?id=VoEZBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA442&lpg=PA442&focus=viewport&dq=editions:n7U-Dq0ClTsC&hl=nl|editor1-last=Blaney|editor1-first=Paul H.|editor3-last=Millon|editor3-first=Theodore|editor2-last=Krueger|editor2-first=Robert F.|edition=Third|title=Oxford textbook of psychopathology|location=NY|publisher=Oxford University Press|pages=441–442|isbn=978-0-19-981177-9|oclc=879552995|accessdate=2015-10-21|archive-date=2021-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405024333/https://books.google.nl/books?id=VoEZBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA442&lpg=PA442&focus=viewport&dq=editions%3An7U-Dq0ClTsC&hl=nl|dead-url=no}}</ref>，以及為人類经常進行的行為，但關於自慰的污名化至今仍然存在。

2013年11月，14岁的馬修·伯德特（Matthew Burdette）被同學拍攝到其自慰，並受到欺凌，他因此[[自殺|自殺]]身亡<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/parenting/we-need-to-talk-about-masturbation-the-last-great-sexual-taboo/article19678627/|title=We need to talk about masturbation, the last great sexual taboo|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=2015-10-21|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820225147/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/parenting/we-need-to-talk-about-masturbation-the-last-great-sexual-taboo/article19678627/|archivedate=2016-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/world-news/americas/boy-scout-14-took-own-life-after-being-mercilessly-bullied-over-viral-sex-act-video-30436799.html|title=Matthew Burdette: Boy Scout, 14, took his own life after being 'bullied' over 'viral video'|work=Irish Independent|accessdate=2016-02-17|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415071712/https://www.independent.ie/world-news/americas/boy-scout-14-took-own-life-after-being-mercilessly-bullied-over-viral-sex-act-video-30436799.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/relationships/bullying-shame-suicide-why-is-masturbation-still-stigmatized/article19730945/|title=Bullying, shame, suicide – why is masturbation still stigmatized?|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=2015-10-21|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820225011/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/relationships/bullying-shame-suicide-why-is-masturbation-still-stigmatized/article19730945/|archivedate=2016-08-20}}</ref>。

1994年，調查研究人員發現半數自慰的男女仍會有罪惡感，證實了當代男女依然無法擺脫自慰的污名（Laumann, et al. 85），另一項兩千年所發表的研究顯示青少年男性經常不敢承認自己會自慰（Halpern, et al. 327）。<ref name="自慰白皮書">[[Planned_Parenthood|Planned Parenthood]], [https://www.plannedparenthood.org/files/5513/9611/7867/masturbation_11-02.pdf Masturbation—From Stigma to Sexual Health] {{Wayback|url=https://www.plannedparenthood.org/files/5513/9611/7867/masturbation_11-02.pdf |date=20161201170718 }} 自慰白皮書— 從污名化到性健康</ref>

